The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, May 11: Seventeen manufacturing sectors, including fertilisers, machine tools, tractors, three-wheelers, motor cycles and electric two-wheelers, registered negative growth in 2007-08 as high interest rate and rising input costs hit the firms. According to a CII survey report, the number of manufacturing sectors registering negative growth increased to about 16.35 per cent in 2007-08 from 11.2 per cent in 2006-07.                             
	 New Delhi, May 11: The government today notified the imposition of export duty on various steel items to discourage exports and enhance domestic availability of steel products.                            
	 New Delhi, May 11: India has asked Canada not to doubt the sincerity of the department of telecoms efforts to help BlackBerry maker Research In Motion in resolving the security issues raised by local authorities and asked the company to co-operate with the communication ministry.                            
	 Dhaka, May 11: Bangladeshs board of investment officials have resumed talks with the Tatas about its proposed $3-billion investment that remained undecided since August 2006.                            
	 London, May 11: Vodafone has no intention of pursuing a bid for South African company MTN, a spokesperson said. Reports in Britains Sunday Telegraph and Sunday Times newspapers said Vodafone was considering making a bid for part or all of MTN, which could cost around 20 billion.                                                                                                                         
